to allies, and that he had failed to provide basic reports to Congress on the office\u2019s operations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/veterans-affairs-investigators-fault-whistleblower-office-created-by-trump-11571925164|title=Veterans Affairs Investigators Fault Whistleblower Office Created by Trump|last=Kesling|first=Ben|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trumps-heralded-whistleblower-office-at-va-has-failed-its-most-basic-mission-watchdog-says/2019/10/24/561e9022-f679-11e9-8cf0-4cc99f74d127_story.html|title=Trump\u2019s heralded whistleblower office at VA is failing in its most basic mission, watchdog says|last=Rein|first=Lisa|date=October 24, 2019|website=The Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://politi.co/2Jh3lYY|title=Florida GOP official accused of 'misdeeds' and retaliation while at VA|first=Matt|last=Dixon|website=Politico PRO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.floridaphoenix.com/blog/reports-newly-picked-fl-republican-party-director-had-troubles-in-washington/|title=Reports: Newly picked FL Republican Party director had troubles in Washington|first=Julie|last=Hauserman}}</ref>\n\n=== Florida Republican Party ===\nIn August 2019, O'Rourke was appointed as the executive director of the [[Republican Party of Florida|Florida Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/6d21566c4855489a9c605f4c3964d379|title=Former Trump official to helm Florida Republican Party|date=August 26, 2019|website=AP NEWS}}</ref> Some Florida Republicans criticized his running of the party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://floridapolitics.com/archives/309996-florida-gop-leaders-begin-calling-for-peter-orourkes-ouster|title=Florida GOP leaders begin calling for Peter O\u2019Rourke\u2019s ousting|first=Jacob|last=Ogles|date=October 31, 2019}}</ref> O'Rourke announced he would resign from his position in March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://floridapolitics.com/archives/321551-executive-director-peter-orourke-exiting-florida-gop|title=Executive director Peter O\u2019Rourke leaving Florida GOP|first=Peter|last=Schorsch|date=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{C-SPAN|peterorourke02}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Wilkie]]<br>{{small|Acting}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Acting [[United States Secretary of Veterans Affairs]]|years=May 29, 2018 \u2013 July 30, 2018}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Robert Wilkie]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Orourke, Peter}}\n[[Category:United States Air Force airmen]]\n[[Category:United States Department of Veterans Affairs officials]]\n[[Category:United States Navy sailors]]\n[[Category:University of Tennessee alumni]]\n[[Category:Trump administration cabinet members]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:United States congressional aides]]\n", "name_user": "1990'sguy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDepartment of Veterans Affairs", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_O%27Rourke_(U.S._government_official)"}
